POSIX-Account-LDAP

POSIX::Account::LDAP and shipped scripts allow you to manager users,
groups and other objects used for POSIX account management in a LDAP
directory.
You can use directly the scripts, or write your own using the module.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc POSIX::Account::LDAP

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/POSIX-Account-LDAP

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=POSIX-Account-LDAP

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/POSIX-Account-LDAP

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/POSIX-Account-LDAP

